  "legacyFile": "blog__2013__04__silhouette-premium-vinyl-giveaway.html",
  "imageCount": 17,
  "body": "<figure>\n\n\n<img src=\"https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5dd0ae59b4b4b35c07faf907/1599952605038-4284N3XNTQ3QBFZZJQUI/12a-DSC_1156-600x398.jpg\"/>\n\n\n</figure>\n\n\n<p>Even though I have had it for quite some time now, it wasn't until the other day that I pulled out the Vinyl starter kit. Instead of creating wall art, I decided to add it to a little box (originally housing chocolates but now I use it for photos) and my mom's mini iPad. I got a turquoise roll of premium vinyl, which is the perfect shade of blue.</p>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<figure>\n\n\n<img src=\"https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5dd0ae59b4b4b35c07faf907/1599952625277-PGAWB1YPOID552GU8MLZ/12b-DSC_1139-600x398.jpg\"/>\n\n\n<figcaption>\n<p>Using the <a href=\"http://www.silhouetteonlinestore.com/?page=view-shape&amp;id=19532\">camera cut file</a> and the <a href=\"http://www.silhouetteonlinestore.com/?page=view-shape&amp;id=18101\">bird cherry blossom doily cut file,</a>I prepared both designs to maximize the use of the vinyl. After the Silhouette finished cutting it, I peeled off all the excess vinyl to reveal the designs. Then I spent about 5 minutes going through and peeling off the little details I didn't want transferring (like the holes in the camera and the spaces in between the branches and flowers.</p>\n</figcaption>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n\n\n<img src=\"https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5dd0ae59b4b4b35c07faf907/1599952644625-SWO3Z7Z9AGE5HD5HVZPQ/12c-DSC_1140-600x398.jpg\"/>\n\n\n<figcaption>\n<p>Next I put applied the transfer paper sticky side down, on top of the design.</p>\n</figcaption>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n\n\n<img src=\"https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5dd0ae59b4b4b35c07faf907/1599952659267-RLY144TZBV2NTCN15SE6/12d-DSC_1141-600x398.jpg\"/>\n\n\n<figcaption>\n<p>I slowly removed the backing (so that I revealed the sticky portion that would go onto the box).</p>\n</figcaption>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n\n\n<img src=\"https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5dd0ae59b4b4b35c07faf907/1599952682550-VWAM1EBCUPB20FATVZ6R/12e-DSC_1142-600x398.jpg\"/>\n\n\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n\n\n<img src=\"https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5dd0ae59b4b4b35c07faf907/1599952704841-OY39C14FAJIXT6JSRLHU/image-asset.jpeg\"/>\n\n\n<figcaption>\n<p>I placed it onto the box and rubbed it in a bit.</p>\n</figcaption>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n\n\n<img src=\"https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5dd0ae59b4b4b35c07faf907/1599952724959-IFUP6GQDQQPEN0BO3F4T/12g-DSC_1144-600x398.jpg\"/>\n\n\n<figcaption>\n<p>Then slowly, I began peeling off the transfer sheet.</p>\n</figcaption>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n\n\n<img src=\"https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5dd0ae59b4b4b35c07faf907/1599952742020-913FF5W7VSRTTD6TNM55/image-asset.jpeg\"/>\n\n\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n\n\n<img src=\"https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5dd0ae59b4b4b35c07faf907/1599952758794-4FS8GSYVFF9RWC10TPA2/image-asset.jpeg\"/>\n\n\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n\n\n<img src=\"https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5dd0ae59b4b4b35c07faf907/1599952770324-Z2ROL49NCXGV7H8O0A5G/12j-DSC_1147-600x398.jpg\"/>\n\n\n<figcaption>\n<p>Didn't want to waste the heart, so I stuck it onto my iPhone case. Love that this stuff is removable.</p>\n</figcaption>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n\n\n<img src=\"https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5dd0ae59b4b4b35c07faf907/1599952786780-LF2B2MW1YTPYVOPWZZV8/12k-DSC_1159-600x398.jpg\"/>\n\n\n<figcaption>\n<p>I thought it all turned out pretty cute, so I moved onto the back of the mini iPad.</p>\n</figcaption>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n\n\n<img src=\"https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5dd0ae59b4b4b35c07faf907/1599952804818-BJT4PIFL1AN3QJ7YVGIJ/12l-DSC_1149-600x398.jpg\"/>\n\n\n</figure>\n\n\n\n\n\n<img alt=\"12m-DSC_1150-600x398.jpg\" src=\"https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5dd0ae59b4b4b35c07faf907/1599952830726-MUEAOCARQPILL4Q1FBJO/12m-DSC_1150-600x398.jpg\">\n</img>\n\n<img alt=\"12n-DSC_1151-600x398.jpg\" src=\"https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5dd0ae59b4b4b35c07faf907/1599952830726-EN06SUM4UBG01SXG95CH/12n-DSC_1151-600x398.jpg\">\n</img>\n\n<img alt=\"12o-DSC_1152-600x398.jpg\" src=\"https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5dd0ae59b4b4b35c07faf907/1599952831283-BCEG4MQXC8TYO67W7ITS/12o-DSC_1152-600x398.jpg\">\n</img>\n\n<img alt=\"12p-DSC_1154-600x398.jpg\" src=\"https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5dd0ae59b4b4b35c07faf907/1599952831288-KRII3OPDD7OFVTIJRN11/12p-DSC_1154-600x398.jpg\">\n</img>\n\n\n\n<p>I'm already scouring the place for more items that \"need\" a little vinyl love. Yesterday I posted a little Vine showing the application <a href=\"https://vine.co/v/bUumjY9HJdq\">here</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<figure>\n\n\n<img src=\"https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5dd0ae59b4b4b35c07faf907/1599952850931-OUM5YZX7SHMLYKQ5MSE5/12q-blogger-promo-april-2013.jpg\"/>\n\n\n</figure>\n\n\n<p>Visit <a href=\"http://www.silhouetteamerica.com/april\">Silhouette</a> and use the promo code: TANGERINE through April 26th to get any of these: (1) 1 Silhouette Portrait™ + 1 roll of black vinyl, 1 roll of white vinyl, and 1 roll of transfer paper: $139.99 (2) 1 Silhouette CAMEO® + 1 roll of black vinyl, 1 roll of white vinyl, and 1 roll of transfer paper: $269.99 (3) All premium vinyl bought outside of a machine bundle is 25% off</p><p>If you haven't caved just yet, perhaps this is a good time - these are some great products! Please <a href=\"http://www.silhouetteamerica.com/april\">click here</a> to take advantage of this month’s discount and don’t forget to enter TANGERINE as the promo code valid through April 26th.</p><p><strong>Once again,</strong> <a href=\"http://www.silhouetteamerica.com/april\"><strong>Silhouette</strong></a><strong> wants to give one of you - my dear readers - a Silhouette Portrait™!</strong></p><p><strong>GIVEAWAY: Open to U.S. residents only - To enter, just leave a comment with what you would cut from the vinyl and what you would stick it on! </strong>Giveaway will close on Saturday, April 20th at 8am and a random winner will be selected and announced here shortly after. Good luck everyone! UPDATED: GIVEAWAY IS NOW CLOSED. The winner is #90: Ilissa says: April 18, 2013 at 6:45 pm</p><p>I’d cut a bunch of cute stuff for my daughters binder and our window as decals!!</p><p>CONGRATS Ilissa! Please send us your mailing address so we can pass it along to Silhouette.</p><p><strong>Remember you can still use the discount code TANGERINE through April 26th!</strong></p>"
